-- Australia's Envestra gets takeover bid from Cheung Kong
-- By Maggie Lu Yueyang
-- Thu May 08, 2014 03:45AM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, May 8 (Reuters) - Australia's Envestra Ltd <ENV.AX> said on Thursday it has received a conditional takeover offer from Hong Kong's Cheung Kong Group <0001.HK>, valuing the natural gas distributor at A$2.37 billion ($2.21 billion) and trumping an earlier bid from Australian Pipeline Ltd (APA).

Cheung Kong, which currently holds a 17.5 percent stake in Envestra, proposed a cash offer of A$1.32 per share, Envestra said in a statement after the market close.